Flow steps: 
1. User requests OAuth token from Apigee (OKAPI)
2. User calls main API with Employee ID + Token
3. Apigee authenticates and routes request
4. Employee Info Microservice receives request
5. Microservice sends XML request to Workday
6. Workday returns XML response
7. Microservice:
- Retries up to 3 times if Workday is unavailable
- Converts XML to JSON
8. JSON published to AWS Kinesis (encrypted via KMS)
9. Fanout Microservice:
- Reads event
- Checks data classification (Unrestricted / Restricted / Confidential)
- Masks sensitive fields
10. Masked data sent to AWS SQS
11. Outbound Adapter reads from SQS
12. Response delivered back to user
